    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, what do you mean it's \"favorable\"? They're literally saying they can just hit us with a 5% increase at the start of the month and we won't even get a heads up. That sounds like the opposite of stable. If they do that during a busy month, our margins are basically gone. \n\nAre you sure there isn't some other part of the section that says we have to agree to it first? I'm reading it and it looks like they have total unilateral control during those months.",
